"title": "8438: giving, of time",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8438: giving, of time",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>People are stewards of a deposit of time given by God, and will be held responsible for the way in which they use it.</p>\n<h2>Time is governed by God</h2>\n<h3>God determines every lifespan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job14:5\">JOB 14:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:15\">PSA 31:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:16-Ps74:17\">PSA 74:16–74:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:16\">PSA 139:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:26\">ACT 17:26</a></p>\n<h3>God will demand an account of how time has been spent</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:17\">ECC 3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:36\">MAT 12:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:3-1Pet4:5\">1PE 4:3–4:5</a></p>\n<h2>Time may be squandered</h2>\n<h3>In ungodly living</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:3\">1PE 4:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:25\">JOL 2:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:2-Eph2:3\">EPH 2:2–2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5-Col3:7\">COL 3:5–3:7</a></p>\n<h3>By neglecting God-given opportunities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:20\">JER 8:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:4\">PRO 20:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:11-Matt25:12\">MAT 25:11–25:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:25\">LUK 13:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:44\">LUK 19:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:25\">ACT 24:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:21\">REV 2:21</a></p>\n<h2>Time may be saved</h2>\n<h3>By understanding its brevity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:12\">PSA 90:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:35\">JHN 12:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:29-1Cor7:31\">1CO 7:29–7:31</a></p>\n<h3>By remembering its uncertainty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:4\">JHN 9:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:5-Eccl8:7\">ECC 8:5–8:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:13-Jas4:15\">JAS 4:13–4:15</a></p>\n<h3>By making the most of present opportunities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:16\">EPH 5:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:6\">PSA 32:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:1\">ECC 12:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:14\">EST 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:17\">MAT 4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:15\">MRK 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:1-2Cor6:2\">2CO 6:1–6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:10\">GAL 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:5\">COL 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:7-Heb3:13\">HEB 3:7–3:13</a></p>\n<h3>By allocating it wisely</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:32\">1CH 12:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:13-Exod18:26\">EXO 18:13–18:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:1-Acts6:4\">ACT 6:1–6:4</a></p>\n<h2>Time is to be spent wisely</h2>\n<h3>In worship and meditation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:164\">PSA 119:164</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:4\">PSA 4:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:17\">PSA 55:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:40\">LAM 3:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:10\">DAN 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:13\">DAN 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:35\">MRK 1:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:28\">1CO 11:28</a></p>\n<h3>In work</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:23\">PSA 104:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:9\">EXO 20:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:13\">DEU 5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:6\">ROM 13:6</a></p>\n<h3>In rest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:8-Exod20:10\">EXO 20:8–20:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:29\">LEV 16:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:31\">MRK 6:31</a></p>\n<h3>With one's family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:5\">DEU 24:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:7\">DEU 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:9\">ECC 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:4\">1TI 3:4</a></p>\n<h3>In fellowship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:7\">1CO 16:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:7\">ACT 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:25\">HEB 10:25</a></p>\n<h2>Time is to be allocated according to priorities</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:41-Luke10:42\">LUK 10:41–10:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1-Ps1:3\">PSA 1:1–1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:2-Hag1:4\">HAG 1:2–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:33\">MAT 6:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:46-Acts13:47\">ACT 13:46–13:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:16-Acts17:17\">ACT 17:16–17:17</a></p>",
